FBIS4-10802 "drlat075_b_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 Haiti Deputy: Implement Article 149 To Avoid Explosion Deputy: Implement Article 149 To Avoid Explosion FL1804175494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 18 Apr 94 FL1804175494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Excerpt] Cap-Haitien Deputy Jacques Lafleur says the Haitian parliament must strive to resolve the crisis in order to avoid a social explosion. Lafleur calls on his peers not to wait for the solution to come from abroad. The country must be saved, he said before concluding, quote: If President Aristide refuses to appoint a new prime minister, the parliament must implement Article 149 of the Constitution. [no ending quote as heard] [passage omitted]
